NUMBER 3402
NAME Abandoned Dig, Upper Shaft
DEEPCAVE
REGION 150
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A dusty ledge circles the shaft, approximately one hundred feet or so beneath the surface. It is wide enough for several people to comfortable stand upon, although you can see nothing of great interest here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;## Items ##
; ## Exits ##
EXIT ABOVE 3400
; ## Special scripting ##

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You conduct a careful search of the area.%c[Round: 10 sec]
 ECHO OTHERS %n inspects the area around %i carefully.
 EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
 IFVAR DIGDOORSEQ = 1
  ECHO PLAYER You notice that the top of the doorway below your feet is blocked by loose rocks and dirt.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DIG -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You dig.%c[Round: 5 sec]
 ECHO OTHERS %n digs.
 EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
 IFVAR DIGDOORSEQ = 1
  ECHO ALL Loose dirt and rock tumbles down the shaft at your feet.
  EQUAL DIGDOORSEQ 2
  AFFECT 3403
  ECHO ALL A hail of loose dirt and rock tumbles down from above!
  DAMAGEALL CRUSH 10 %n is struck!
  AFFECT 3404
  ECHO ALL A hail of loose dirt and rock tumbles down from above!
  DAMAGEALL CRUSH 15 %n is struck!
  AFFECT 3405
  ECHO ALL A hail of loose dirt and rock tumbles down from above!
  DAMAGEALL CRUSH 20 %n is struck!
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER There is hardly any result to your digging.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 8
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You step gingerly onto the platform.
 ECHO OTHERS %n steps gingerly onto the platform.
 MOVE 3401
 AFFECT 3401
 ECHO OTHERS %n steps onto the platform.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EXAMINE 8
 IFITEM 8
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER On the platform you see...
  SHOWROOM 3401
 ENDIF
ENDIF
; #### end of room #####

NUMBER 3403
NAME Abandoned Dig, Middle Shaft
DEEPCAVE
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This seems to be about the halfway point of the shaft, judging by the fall and play of the platform ropes. Remarkably, an ancient stone doorway abuts a circular ledge at this level. The door displays peculiar dimensions, being extraordinarily tall and slender.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;## Items ##
;door
ITEM 0 943 ADJ1=317 ADJ2=210 ADJ3=312 VAL1=999 VAL2=3406 VAL3=999 CLOSED LOCKED
; ## Exits ##
EXIT ABOVE 3402
; ## Special scripting ##
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The doorway, which spans only a two and a half foot width, rises thirty or forty feet in height. It is constructed of a single immense slab of cut and dressed stone, and would be considered a marvel in any age.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
 IFVAR DIGDOORTIME ! TIM
  IFITEM 0 OPEN
   EQUAL DIGDOORSEQ 0
   CLOSE 0
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 0
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR DIGDOORSEQ = 2
  OPEN 0
  ECHO PLAYER You pull the door open.
  ECHO OTHERS %n pulls the door open.
  EQUAL DIGDOORTIME TIM
 ELSE
  ECHO OTHERS %n tugs at the door to no avail.
  IFVAR DIGDOORSEQ = 1
   ECHO PLAYER It seems to be stuck from above.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER It seems to be too heavy to move.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

